title: Fire Island National Seashore: Fees & Passes
body: Explore This Park    Plan Your Visit     Basic Information     Fees & Passes               Fees & Passes          Â    There is no fee to enter Fire Island National Seashore but plan to pay parking and/or transportation fees to get to most parts of Fire Island. National Parks and Federal Recreation Lands Pass Series If you plan to visit other national parks with an entrance fee, learn more about America the Beautiful - The National Parks and Federal Recreational Lands Pass series. The American the Beautiful Series Access, Senior, and Annual Military passes may be obtained at Fire Island National Seashore's headquarters located at 120 Laurel Street in Patchogue, New York. To Obtain a Senior Pass A check or money order for $10 made out to "National Park Service" is required to cover the cost of processing the application. Cash and credit card payment cannot be accepted. For More Information  Seashore Headquarters 631-687-4750 Open year-round 9:00 am to 4:00 pm, closed federal holidays.
